name: 180 Decibel
description:
The largest baby born in the world is the baby blue whale. These babies are growing amazingly; In the first 7 months of life, they drink about 100 gallons (about 379 liters) of milk from their mother daily.
Blue regiments can produce different sounds. Male whales make 180 decibel cries to attract female whales.  These cries can be detected from a distance of more than 800 km. The sound of a blue whale is the loudest sound a living thing can make.
